<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871022-0100 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:Bedford Computer Corp.</HL><DD> 10/22/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> BANKRUPTCIES (BCY) </IN><TEXT>   Bedford Computer Corp. said a U.S. bankruptcy court in New Hampshire approved a previously announced reorganization plan that will enable the company to emerge from bankruptcy proceedings.    As previously reported, the plan calls for most of Bedford's debt to be converted to stock. Current shareholders will own about 9% of the reorganized company.    The Londonderry, N.H., maker of electronic publishing systems filed for protection under Chapter 11 of the federal Bankruptcy Code in November 1985. </TEXT></DOC>